Question No: 1
Single File Programming Question
Create a Student class with properties: name, marks, and a method getGrade() which returns:

'A' if marks ≥ 90
'B' if marks ≥ 75
'C' otherwise
Take student name and marks from the console input, then display their grade.

Input format :
The first line is the name

The second line is the mark

Output format :
Refer the sample output

Sample test cases :
Input 1 :
ravi
55
Output 1 :
ravi's Grade: C

===============================
         Program
===============================
process.stdin.on('data', data =>{
    let line = data.toString().trim().split('\n');
    let name = line[0];
    let mark = parseInt(line[1]);
    
    class Student{
        constructor(name,mark){
            this.name = name;
            this.mark = mark;
        }
        getGrade(){
            if(this.mark >= 90){
                return "A";
            }else if(this.mark >= 75){
                return "B";
            }else{
                return "C";
            }
        }
    }
    let student = new Student(name,mark);
    console.log(`${student.name}'s Grade: ${student.getGrade()}`);
})



Question No: 2
Single File Programming Question
Build an application with Javascript where you need find the bill for the purchased things



Create a class with name, price and quantity as the attributes. 

Create object, feed the inputs, find the total bill

Input format :
The first line is the name

The second line is the price of a thing

The third line is the quantity

Sample test cases :
Input 1 :
alex
50
4
Output 1 :
Total bill for alex: 200

===============================
          Program
===============================

process.stdin.on('data', data=>{
    let line = data.toString().trim().split('\n');
    let name = line[0];
    let price = parseInt(line[1]);
    let quantity = parseInt(line[2]);
    
    class Bill{
        constructor(name,price,quantity){
            this.name = name;
            this.price = price;
            this.quantity = quantity;
        }
        getBill(){
            return this.price*this.quantity;
        }
    }
    let bill = new Bill(name,price,quantity);
    console.log(`Total bill for ${bill.name}: ${bill.getBill()}`)
})


Question No: 3
Single File Programming Question
Create an Employee class with name, basicSalary, and bonus.

Add a method getTotalSalary() that returns total salary = basicSalary + bonus.

Read all values from input and print the total salary of the employee.

Input format :
The first line is the name

The second line is the basicSalary

The third line is the bonus

Output format :
Refer the sample output

Sample test cases :
Input 1 :
virat
34000
3000
Output 1 :
virat's Total Salary: 37000


================================
           Program
================================
process.stdin.on('data', data =>{
    let line = data.toString().trim().split('\n');
    let name =line[0];
    let salary =parseInt(line[1]);
    let bonus = parseInt(line[2]);
    
    class Employee{
        constructor(name,salary,bonus){
            this.name = name;
            this.salary = salary;
            this.bonus = bonus;
        }
        getTotalSalary(){
            return this.salary+this.bonus;
        }
    }
    let Emp = new Employee(name,salary,bonus);
    console.log(`${Emp.name}'s Total Salary: ${Emp.getTotalSalary()}`)
})
